00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:01,000
 Do you know what's in your hands?

382
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:05,000
 It may not be a very powerful weapon.

383
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,000
 But when God wants to use you,

384
00:19:08,000 --> 00:19:11,000
 it becomes something that can be used.

385
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:16,000
 The Bible says, "Those who are faithful in small things

386
00:19:16,000 --> 00:19:19,000
 will be faithful in great things."

387
00:19:19,000 --> 00:19:22,000
 Jesus said, "When I chose people,

388
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:26,000
 I chose those who were faithful in small things."

389
00:19:26,000 --> 00:19:28,000
 When you cook, are you faithful?

390
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:31,000
 When you buy food, are you not being discouraged?

391
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,000
 When I was a doctor,

392
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:39,000
 I thought, "I have seen such a normal disease."

393
00:19:39,000 --> 00:19:44,000
 I have seen a patient in such a small clinic.

394
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:47,000
 But are you faithful in small things?

395
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:52,000
 If so, God may put you in a big thing one day

396
00:19:52,000 --> 00:20:00,000
 to show His ability to do great things.

397
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:04,000
 So in our small things every day,

398
00:20:04,000 --> 00:20:07,000
 we must be faithful,

399
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:09,000
 and be faithful to God.

400
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:16,000
 Sometimes God will transform you,

401
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:21,000
 prepare you,

402
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:26,000
 so that you are more suitable for great things.

403
00:20:26,000 --> 00:20:30,000
 These kinds of training are usually done

404
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:34,000
 when you are most unhappy.

405
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:37,000
 I will tell you an example later.

406
00:20:37,000 --> 00:20:41,000
 After I was a doctor for three years,

407
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:45,000
 I decided to leave my position

408
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,000
 and go to Canada to do a doctorate.

409
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,000
 But I was not selected or recruited to Harvard

410
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:55,000
 to be a Canadian.

411
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:58,000
 I went to a place called Calgary,

412
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,000
 where I did a PhD.

413
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:02,000
 I asked myself,

414
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,000
 "What did I do wrong?

415
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:06,000
 Why was I selected to be trained

416
00:21:06,000 --> 00:21:11,000
 in such a small and unpopular place?"

417
00:21:11,000 --> 00:21:15,000
 In such a small place,

418
00:21:15,000 --> 00:21:21,000
 I trained myself how to live independently,

419
00:21:21,000 --> 00:21:25,000
 how to think independently,

420
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:28,000
 and not necessarily follow the boss' instructions.

421
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:32,000
 I trained myself to live in a cold,

422
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:39,000
 and unpopular environment.

423
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:44,000
 Often, when we think that life is a low,

424
00:21:44,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 and encountering a lot of difficulties,

425
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:50,000
 God is preparing you,

426
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:54,000
 preparing you to do something big.

427
00:21:54,000 --> 00:21:58,000
 God is preparing you to live a life

428
00:21:58,000 --> 00:22:04,000
 where you can be a living testimony.

429
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 God did not choose us because we have a shirt,

430
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:15,000
 but because our daily life is like a document

431
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:18,000
 that proves that we are loyal to Him.

432
00:22:18,000 --> 00:22:21,000
 Although it is a small thing,

433
00:22:21,000 --> 00:22:23,000
 we are loyal to Him.

434
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:25,000
 The gentleman behind me is very good.

435
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:27,000
 Every time I turn around,

436
00:22:27,000 --> 00:22:29,000
 the screen will turn to show me

437
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:31,000
 what I wrote.

438
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,000
 Thank you.

439
00:22:33,000 --> 00:22:35,000
 Lastly,

440
00:22:35,000 --> 00:22:39,000
 the seventh thing to note and prepare is

441
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:43,000
 that you must still have a humble heart.

442
00:22:43,000 --> 00:22:45,000
 A humble heart.

443
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:48,000
 It is a very easy mistake.

444
00:22:48,000 --> 00:22:51,000
 When you have a little bit of success,

445
00:22:51,000 --> 00:22:54,000
 you will think, "I can do it."

446
00:22:54,000 --> 00:22:57,000
 When you reach the first level,

447
00:22:57,000 --> 00:23:00,000
 you will realize that you are not bad.

448
00:23:00,000 --> 00:23:03,000
 But this is the time when we fall easily

449
00:23:03,000 --> 00:23:07,000
 because we lack humility.

450
00:23:07,000 --> 00:23:10,000
 Lack of humility is because we know

451
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,000
 that we can stand still today

452
00:23:12,000 --> 00:23:15,000
 because we are like a grapevine

453
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:17,000
 that is tied to a branch.

454
00:23:17,000 --> 00:23:24,000
 Jesus said that if the grapevine is not tied to the tree,

455
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,000
 you will not be able to bear fruit.

456
00:23:26,000 --> 00:23:30,000
 You will not be able to continue to play your role.

457
00:23:30,000 --> 00:23:32,000
 So be humble and...

458
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:35,000
 I must not turn my face to you.

459
00:23:35,000 --> 00:23:37,000
 Be humble and dependent.

460
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:40,000
 He said that you must rely on Him

461
00:23:40,000 --> 00:23:42,000
 and be humble.

462
00:23:42,000 --> 00:23:44,000
 The seven things...

463
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:46,000
 You don't remember which seven things I mentioned.

464
00:23:46,000 --> 00:23:48,000
 Usually, we only mention two things.

465
00:23:48,000 --> 00:23:50,000
 What is the first thing?

466
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:53,000
 The first thing is that you must love Him

467
00:23:53,000 --> 00:23:56,000
 with all your heart and all your mind.

468
00:23:56,000 --> 00:24:00,000
 Then you must be willing to be called.

469
00:24:00,000 --> 00:24:02,000
 Like Isaiah,

470
00:24:02,000 --> 00:24:05,000
 "Lord, I am in this place. Please show me."

471
00:24:05,000 --> 00:24:08,000
 Then you must see what you have

472
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:11,000
 and what you can use.

473
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:15,000
 Then you must be loyal in small things.

474
00:24:15,000 --> 00:24:17,000
 When you are in trouble,

475
00:24:17,000 --> 00:24:21,000
 you must accept His training and His teaching.

476
00:24:21,000 --> 00:24:24,000
 Finally, you must use your daily life

477
00:24:24,000 --> 00:24:26,000
 as a witness

478
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:30,000
 and become your true friend.

479
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:34,000
 Finally, when you have a little bit of success,

480
00:24:34,000 --> 00:24:36,000
 you must continue to be humble

481
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:38,000
 and depend on Him.

482
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:40,000
 You must be humble.

483
00:24:40,000 --> 00:24:42,000
 This is what I think.

484
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:45,000
 How can you make your ordinary life

485
00:24:45,000 --> 00:24:48,000
 become extraordinary?

486
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:50,000
 Today, I want to share with you

487
00:24:50,000 --> 00:24:53,000
 a photo that I haven't shown to anyone for a long time.

488
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,000
 This is me.

489
00:24:55,000 --> 00:24:57,000
 I grew up in an ordinary family.

490
00:24:57,000 --> 00:24:59,000
 The one sitting in the middle is me.

491
00:24:59,000 --> 00:25:02,000
 The one holding me is my younger brother

492
00:25:02,000 --> 00:25:04,000
 and my cousin.

493
00:25:04,000 --> 00:25:07,000
 Our family is not a rich family.

494
00:25:07,000 --> 00:25:09,000
 It is definitely not a rich family.

495
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:13,000
 My grandfather was a car repairman.

496
00:25:13,000 --> 00:25:15,000
 He was a sprayer.

497
00:25:15,000 --> 00:25:19,000
 He opened a small workshop in Wanchai, Hong Kong.

498
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:23,000
 My mother was a small employee in a bank.

499
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:28,000
 It is strange that she worked in a big bank.

500
00:25:28,000 --> 00:25:31,000
 There is a big bank in Hong Kong, UOB.

501
00:25:31,000 --> 00:25:34,000
 She was a small employee.

502
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:37,000
 She only studied until she graduated from primary school.

503
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:41,000
 My father was a shopkeeper

504
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:45,000
 who sold glasses.

505
00:25:45,000 --> 00:25:48,000
 He was a very unremarkable person.

506
00:25:48,000 --> 00:25:50,000
 I still remember when I was young,

507
00:25:50,000 --> 00:25:52,000
 I lived in Wanchai.

508
00:25:52,000 --> 00:25:55,000
 I could smell the smell of car spray.

509
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,000
 In Wanchai, Lohkak,

510
00:25:58,000 --> 00:26:02,000
 there were many bars.

511
00:26:02,000 --> 00:26:10,000
 The US military kept going to Vietnam to fight.

512
00:26:10,000 --> 00:26:12,000
 After 6 weeks of fighting,

513
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:16,000
 he would come to Hong Kong and drink a big glass of wine in Wanchai.

514
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:18,000
 Then he would go to the bar.

515
00:26:18,000 --> 00:26:21,000
 You can imagine what he did.

516
00:26:21,000 --> 00:26:26,000
 I grew up in this kind of red-light district.

517
00:26:26,000 --> 00:26:33,000
 I think I am not particularly good-looking.

518
00:26:33,000 --> 00:26:35,000
 Although I am a little good-looking,

519
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:37,000
 I am not particularly good-looking.

