00:28:01,000 --> 00:28:03,000
 Everything seemed to be going well,

547
00:28:03,000 --> 00:28:06,000
 but I had to give you some difficulties.

548
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:10,000
 So when I was training,

549
00:28:10,000 --> 00:28:13,000
 I was doing my gastroenterology,

550
00:28:13,000 --> 00:28:16,000
 I was very unhappy and difficult.

551
00:28:16,000 --> 00:28:22,000
 I had to resign my job and go to Canada to do my PhD.

552
00:28:22,000 --> 00:28:26,000
 So in the three years in Canada,

553
00:28:26,000 --> 00:28:30,000
 I kept asking myself if I had made the wrong decision.

554
00:28:30,000 --> 00:28:32,000
 I didn't want a doctor's job.

555
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:34,000
 I went to Canada to be a student.

556
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:38,000
 The salary I got was less than a third of what I got as a doctor.

557
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:41,000
 It was a cold place.

558
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:50,000
 It was a very difficult environment for me to grow up.

559
00:28:50,000 --> 00:28:53,000
 The worst thing was that when I got my PhD,

560
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:55,000
 it was 1992,

561
00:28:55,000 --> 00:28:59,000
 when Canada was just entering the country's economic downturn.

562
00:28:59,000 --> 00:29:05,000
 I wrote ten letters to ten different universities and hospitals in Canada.

563
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,000
 None of them replied to me,

564
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:10,000
 saying that they could hire me to continue working there.

565
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:14,000
 I thought, "Oh no, I'm graduating and I'm unemployed.

566
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:18,000
 I can't go back to work in the hospital."

567
00:29:18,000 --> 00:29:22,000
 At that moment, Hong Kong called me and said,

568
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:25,000
 "Your boss has left.

569
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:28,000
 Do you still want to come back to work?"

570
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:35,000
 That's how I came back to Hong Kong in 1992.

571
00:29:35,000 --> 00:29:37,000
 I was working at a Chinese university.

572
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:40,000
 I thought I would be working there for a year or two,

573
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:43,000
 because I thought I wouldn't stay in Hong Kong for long.

574
00:29:43,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 But I worked there for 35 years.

575
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:53,000
 It was a completely unexpected arrangement.

576
00:29:53,000 --> 00:29:56,000
 As I worked there, things started to improve.

577
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:59,000
 I started to see some achievements.

578
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:01,000
 The articles we published were viewed by more people.

579
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:06,000
 I trained more dentists and became a team.

580
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:09,000
 Ten years later, in 2003,

581
00:30:09,000 --> 00:30:11,000
 a big change occurred.

582
00:30:11,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 Everyone remembers SARS.

583
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:17,000
 It was a completely unprepared environment.

584
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:21,000
 When we thought we had some achievements,

585
00:30:21,000 --> 00:30:24,000
 God gave us a surprise.

586
00:30:24,000 --> 00:30:28,000
 It turned out that what we knew was very limited.

587
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:34,000
 We thought we had a lot of medical skills and experience.

588
00:30:34,000 --> 00:30:37,000
 But when a new virus appeared,

589
00:30:37,000 --> 00:30:40,000
 we were completely at a loss.

590
00:30:40,000 --> 00:30:44,000
 I remember telling myself and the reporters,

591
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 "I feel like I'm carrying 100 eggs in my heart.

592
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,000
 I can't let it fall to the ground."

593
00:30:52,000 --> 00:30:55,000
 Each egg is a patient of mine.

594
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:59,000
 25% of the patients are doctors and nurses.

595
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:03,000
 I don't want to see any life

596
00:31:03,000 --> 00:31:06,000
 because we don't know how to deal with it.

597
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:09,000
 So we lost these precious lives.

598
00:31:09,000 --> 00:31:13,000
 At that moment, we prayed together and told God,

599
00:31:13,000 --> 00:31:16,000
 "Please don't let my ignorance

600
00:31:16,000 --> 00:31:20,000
 make us abandon a life,

601
00:31:20,000 --> 00:31:22,000
 a precious life."

602
00:31:22,000 --> 00:31:24,000
 At that moment, the whole room,

603
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 the whole room of my office was filled with Christians.

604
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 Because we really had a lot of difficulties in our hearts.

605
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:32,000
 We didn't know how to solve them.

606
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:36,000
 But when we felt we were the most incompetent,

607
00:31:36,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 when we felt we lacked wisdom,

608
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:42,000
 when we were the weakest,

609
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:46,000
 God showed His strength.

610
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:48,000
 A miracle happened.

611
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 We started to pray for each patient in the ward every day.

612
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:57,000
 Then we started to see the restoration.

613
00:31:57,000 --> 00:32:00,000
 Then there was the story of Sars.

614
00:32:00,000 --> 00:32:02,000
 You may have heard of it.

615
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 In this transition,

616
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:09,000
 people thought, "You can be a leader.

617
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:13,000
 Why don't you do more leadership work?"

618
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:16,000
 In 2008, when Sichuan had a big earthquake,

619
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:19,000
 I took a group of classmates to Wenchuan,

620
00:32:19,000 --> 00:32:22,000
 the place where the earthquake was the most severe.

621
00:32:22,000 --> 00:32:27,000
 We went to the town.

622
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,000
 You can see the bell is broken.

623
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:31,000
 Many buildings have collapsed.

624
00:32:31,000 --> 00:32:34,000
 The buildings next to us were originally three-story buildings,

625
00:32:34,000 --> 00:32:37,000
 but now they are on the ground.

626
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:40,000
 At that time, I started to feel

627
00:32:40,000 --> 00:32:43,000
 that what I could do

628
00:32:43,000 --> 00:32:45,000
 or what God wanted me to do

629
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:50,000
 was more than sitting in the office or in the door of the clinic to see the earthquake.

630
00:32:50,000 --> 00:32:53,000
 I can lead a group of students

631
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 to make them more useful people in society.

632
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:01,000
 I thought, although I was much older than them,

633
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:04,000
 I was actually at the same age as their father,

634
00:33:04,000 --> 00:33:08,000
 but they didn't seem to give up on me and their generation.

635
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:11,000
 They became my good friends.

636
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:14,000
 So I became a principal.

637
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:18,000
 It was a big surprise to become a principal.

638
00:33:18,000 --> 00:33:26,000
 I had never studied education.

639
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:29,000
 I only studied medicine.

640
00:33:29,000 --> 00:33:34,000
 I had never studied leadership or politics.

641
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:39,000
 But I was completely surprised to become a principal.

642
00:33:39,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 In this surprise, I found that I had to face many problems every day.

643
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:49,000
 I never imagined how to face them.

644
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:52,000
 Although everyone was very happy at the graduation ceremony,

645
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:58,000
 the graduation ceremony of our university was the most terrifying day of the year.

646
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:01,000
 Because there were protests and demonstrations that day.

647
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:08,000
 Many reporters came to film our embarrassing scenes

648
00:34:08,000 --> 00:34:11,000
 and asked me some embarrassing questions.

649
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 So every year, November is my biggest worry.

650
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:23,000
 I didn't know what would happen that day.

651
00:34:23,000 --> 00:34:29,000
 I didn't know what kind of surprises would happen that day.

652
00:34:29,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 I just passed by the principal's office for seven and a half years.

653
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:41,000
 I don't know why I came to this place.

654
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 The story I just told you

655
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:50,000
 is to show that I am a very honest person.

656
00:34:50,000 --> 00:34:55,000
 I am a very ordinary person.

657
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:59,000
 I am an ordinary person.

658
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:02,000
 But just like you,

659
00:35:02,000 --> 00:35:06,000
 our ordinary can become God's extraordinary.

660
00:35:06,000 --> 00:35:12,000
 Our weak can become God's manifestation of His ability.

661
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:21,000
 Our ignorant can become God's wisdom.

662
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:24,000
 Sister Ling, have you ever thought that

663
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:27,000
 even if you are very ordinary,

664
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:31,000
 as long as God is by your side,

665
00:35:31,000 --> 00:35:33,000
 as long as He is holding you in His hands,

666
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:37,000
 one day you may do something great.

667
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:39,000
 Or even in the eyes of others,

668
00:35:39,000 --> 00:35:41,000
 it may not seem like a big deal.

669
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:45,000
 But in His eyes, it seems like a big deal.

670
00:35:45,000 --> 00:35:49,000
 So today's Bible reminds us again

671
00:35:49,000 --> 00:35:53,000
 not to underestimate our own judgment.

672
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:59,000
 He says, if God wants to choose,

673
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,000
 He will choose those who are humble,

674
00:36:02,000 --> 00:36:04,000
 those who are ungrateful.

675
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:06,000
 This is in Acts 4, verse 6.

676
00:36:06,000 --> 00:36:10,000
 He says He will resist those who are arrogant,

677
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 but will be kind to those who are humble.

678
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:19,000
 Then He says in Columbus' 12th chapter,

679
00:36:19,000 --> 00:36:20,000
 9th chapter,

680
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:23,000
 "My grace is sufficient for you;

681
00:36:23,000 --> 00:36:30,000
 my power is more perfect in the body of the weak."

682
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:34,000
 It is not about how much power we have.

683
00:36:34,000 --> 00:36:37,000
 It is not about our ability that counts.

684
00:36:37,000 --> 00:36:39,000
 It is about our availability.

685
00:36:39,000 --> 00:36:42,000
 We are willing to be used by God.

686
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:45,000
 It is like the saying,

687
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:48,000
 "Lord, I am here, please show me."

688
00:36:48,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 Do you have this kind of mind today?

689
